WEBVTT

00:02.709 --> 00:05.709
-Two on the glass.
-Alright, thanks Nathan.

00:05.750 --> 00:07.709
-No problem.
-[Callaghan]: I appreciate it.

00:07.750 --> 00:09.959
-[Gerry]: Hey! I heard we had
some alumni drop in.

00:10.000 --> 00:12.208
Nathan, Cameron. Wow.
-Hey Sir.

00:12.250 --> 00:14.792
-Really proud of you guys.
-Oh yeah, are we ever.

00:14.834 --> 00:17.000
Especially you, Nathan.
I knew you had it in ya.

00:17.041 --> 00:19.250
-Ha, sir, you told me to
give up hockey.

00:19.291 --> 00:21.792
-Reverse psychology. And it
worked. So you're welcome...

00:21.834 --> 00:24.834
Mr. Calder.
-Okay, well thanks for
dropping in guys.

00:24.875 --> 00:29.542
-Yeah. Hey, I'm thinking of
going to Colorado Nathan,
so ah...

00:29.583 --> 00:33.250
How about some tickets?
-Mmm, all sold out.

00:33.291 --> 00:35.333
-[Gerry quietly]: What?

00:36.750 --> 00:40.125
-I could probably get you a few
tickets to my college game sir.

00:40.166 --> 00:43.250
-What about exhibition?
-Sold out.

00:43.291 --> 00:45.500
-Really easy for me to
get you tickets.

00:45.542 --> 00:49.667
-College hockey. And I guess,
ah, next year's games are all
sold out?

00:49.709 --> 00:51.917
-Yeah, crazy huh?
-[Gerry]: Yeah.

00:51.959 --> 00:55.250
-Okay, well thanks guys. Good
to see you. See you again soon.
-[Gerry]: Yeah, good to see ya.

00:55.291 --> 00:58.250
-Thanks Cameron.
-[Nathan]: Yeah, you too.
-Alright, see ya.

00:58.291 --> 01:00.709
Hey!
-So, how come you don't want
to watch me play?

01:00.750 --> 01:03.041
-Nope, never said I don't
want to watch you play.

01:03.083 --> 01:05.375
I would love to come.

01:05.417 --> 01:08.000
Where are your games?

01:08.041 --> 01:11.333
-It's only a 40 minute drive.
-Mmm, then ya add traffic.

01:11.375 --> 01:13.625
And then...
-I get it.

01:13.667 --> 01:16.083
[♪ Music]
-Okay.

01:16.125 --> 01:18.917
♪ I'm awesome, no you're
not dude, don't lie ♪

01:18.959 --> 01:21.792
♪ I'm awesome, I'm driving
around in my mom's ride ♪

01:21.834 --> 01:24.083
♪ I'm awesome, a quarter
of my life gone by ♪

01:25.333 --> 01:27.834
♪ I'm awesome ♪

01:28.875 --> 01:31.041
-[Gerry]: Undefeated so far.

01:31.083 --> 01:33.291
Let's just keep this train
rolling.

01:33.333 --> 01:35.500
Starts again with another
good practice.

01:35.542 --> 01:37.959
And I will say, regardless
of the outcome, it has been

01:38.000 --> 01:41.417
a tremendous honour to take
you to an undefeated season.

01:41.458 --> 01:44.750
As I have. Couldn't do it
without Terrence though.

01:44.792 --> 01:50.667
So, Tommy, Jack, your
last game as seniors, maybe...

01:50.709 --> 01:54.125
Your last game, probably,
playing on a team.

01:54.166 --> 01:56.583
'Cause you're not going to play
at college, that's for sure.

01:56.625 --> 01:58.834
Unless you play intramurals
or something. So...

01:58.875 --> 02:03.000
Enjoy the game, take it in as
you watch from the bench.

02:03.041 --> 02:06.333
-Hey coach, I think it's time
for you to cut up some of them
great oranges again.

02:06.375 --> 02:10.750
-Oh, haha, you guys still love
the oranges I do every practice.

02:10.792 --> 02:13.000
-You are very good
at the oranges.

02:13.041 --> 02:15.500
-[Gerry laughs]: I'll get those
going again, as usual.

02:15.542 --> 02:20.667
And you guys do as I kind of...
what I want you to do here.

02:20.709 --> 02:21.792
Okay?

02:23.333 --> 02:26.583
-Alright guys, big game. You
need to stay focused. Alright?

02:26.625 --> 02:30.208
Get your heads in it,
last practice was weak.

02:30.250 --> 02:32.750
Next we gotta work on our
two-three zone. Bring it in.

02:34.917 --> 02:37.709
-[Terrence]: One, two, three
-[All]: Together.

02:40.458 --> 02:42.750
-[Gerry]: I always miss that.

02:42.792 --> 02:45.458
-[Robert makes a gun sound]

02:45.500 --> 02:48.208
Lisa. Dwyer.

02:48.250 --> 02:50.875
[Frustrated]: Gerry!

02:50.917 --> 02:53.500
Simon.
-I'll take that.

02:53.542 --> 02:56.542
[Simon gasps]: Cool,
I love plays.

02:56.583 --> 02:58.792
I didn't know you were an actor.
-Uh huh.

02:58.834 --> 03:01.000
-And a producer...
-Uh huh.

03:01.041 --> 03:03.000
-And a director...
-That's right.
-Stage manager...

03:03.041 --> 03:05.875
-There are a lot of things
people don't know about me.
It runs in the family.

03:05.917 --> 03:09.000
I've dabbled in thespianity
over the years.

03:09.041 --> 03:12.000
-Mmm, my mom dabbled in that
in college. Had a bit of a
window...

03:12.041 --> 03:14.291
-No, I...
-She called it her lady window.

03:14.333 --> 03:17.959
-Opening night, you gonna come?
-I've never been to an
opening night before.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.417
-Well, might I suggest you buy
your tickets good and early?

03:20.458 --> 03:22.709
'Cause it's only a 350 seater.

03:22.750 --> 03:25.417
I think a lot of the people I
studied drama with in college
are gonna come.

03:25.458 --> 03:27.625
I've been working on
this for fifteen years.

03:27.667 --> 03:29.667
-So it must be good.
-Oh, it is.

03:33.959 --> 03:37.041
-God, will this day never end?

03:37.083 --> 03:39.333
[Lisa sighs, frustrated]

03:41.542 --> 03:43.917
[Mouths]: Oh.
What are you doing?

03:43.959 --> 03:47.542
-Shh, shh, shh, shh.
20 second hug.

03:47.583 --> 03:50.083
-[Gerry]: Ugh.
-Relaxes the muscles.

03:50.125 --> 03:54.500
Elevates mood.
Strengthens the immune system.

03:54.542 --> 03:58.083
-What a load of garbage that is.
Oh god.

03:58.125 --> 04:01.917
-[Malik whispers]: 18, 19...
-[Gerry]: What a joke.

04:03.709 --> 04:06.208
-20.
-Wow.

04:06.250 --> 04:08.333
I actually do feel
a little better.

04:10.041 --> 04:13.166
Thank you Mr. Malik.
-Give me a break Lisa,
you don't feel better.

04:13.208 --> 04:15.375
-You like to try?
I prove it to you.

04:15.417 --> 04:17.417
-No thank you.
Don't touch me please.

04:20.083 --> 04:22.333
-You want another one?

04:22.375 --> 04:24.583
-Yes please.
[Lisa laughs]

04:24.625 --> 04:26.875
-Guys...

04:26.917 --> 04:29.083
-[Malik]: Shh, shh, shh.
-Hi. Oh my god.

04:30.250 --> 04:32.834
Seriously?
-[Lisa]: Gerry, get out of here.

04:32.875 --> 04:35.000
-[Gerry whispers]: Oh god.
-Start over.

04:35.041 --> 04:39.333
[♪ Music]

04:39.375 --> 04:42.125
-Hey, what are you doing?

04:42.166 --> 04:44.083
-Coaching, what does
it look like I'm doing?

04:44.125 --> 04:47.250
-[Laughs]: Yeah. Hey, I wanted
to talk to you about the game.

04:47.291 --> 04:49.500
-What?
-Well, you know Syracuse
is coming, right?

04:55.125 --> 04:57.959
-Syracuse Orangemen.

04:58.000 --> 05:00.375
To see Terrence?
-[Bobbi]: Yeah.

05:01.542 --> 05:03.667
-I was supposed to
go to Syracuse.

05:03.709 --> 05:05.917
-For what?
-None of your business.

05:05.959 --> 05:09.458
-Okay, look, all I'm saying is
just don't do what you do.

05:09.500 --> 05:11.750
Okay?
-What do I do?

05:11.792 --> 05:15.125
-Okay, first of all, I didn't do
it like that. Second of all,
don't overwork Terrence.

05:15.166 --> 05:17.166
-Oh! Yeah, 'cause I was
gonna do that.

05:17.208 --> 05:20.125
I was gonna go for a big 10 KM
run with him before the game.

05:20.166 --> 05:22.208
So, cancel that?
-That's not the point.

05:22.250 --> 05:25.417
I'm telling you not to
do what you do.

05:25.458 --> 05:27.625
-Oh! Don't do what I do?
-Yeah.

05:27.667 --> 05:31.041
-Oh! Don't win? Or should
I do what you can't do?

05:31.083 --> 05:33.333
Is that what I should do?
-Just don't do what you do, kay.

05:33.375 --> 05:35.542
-Yeah, okay. I'm going
to get back to coaching.

05:35.583 --> 05:37.834
-Don't do what you do.
-Go away.

05:37.875 --> 05:42.000
-[Bobbi]: Don't do what you do.
-Terrence won't eat them
when they're that big.

05:42.041 --> 05:44.041
He hates the big ones.

05:44.917 --> 05:47.959
-[Robert]: Trudy?
What is this?

05:48.000 --> 05:50.291
-It looks like a flyer.
-[Robert fake laughs]

05:50.333 --> 05:53.041
-I know what it is. A better
question might be...

05:53.083 --> 05:57.250
What is this flyer doing in the
recycling bins next to the staff
mailboxes?

05:57.291 --> 06:00.125
-Oh, who would do that?
-Busted!

06:00.166 --> 06:02.125
Someone with the initials
TW, that's who.

06:02.166 --> 06:04.750
-Tiger Woods.
-Oh, does he work at
the school now?

06:04.792 --> 06:07.000
[Fake laughs]: No.

06:07.041 --> 06:11.041
You know who does?
T-rudy W-alsh. TW.

06:11.083 --> 06:14.125
-You put the initials of every
staff member on the backs
of those flyers?

06:14.166 --> 06:17.667
-You're darn tootin' I did.
'Cause that way I know
who my real friends are.

06:17.709 --> 06:20.041
Not you.
-So, the recycling
bin was full then?

06:21.834 --> 06:25.834
-Trudy, this is my theatrical
debut. If you can't tell, it
means a lot to me.

06:25.875 --> 06:27.917
I could use a bit of support.

06:29.333 --> 06:31.542
-Wait!

06:31.583 --> 06:34.458
-Wait! You are going to be
performing? On a stage?
In front of people?

06:34.500 --> 06:36.959
-Yeah, matter of fact I am.

06:37.041 --> 06:39.208
-[Laughs]: I am definitely
seeing that.

06:39.250 --> 06:42.458
-Okay! Tickets are five bucks.
-Can you lend me five bucks?

06:42.500 --> 06:45.166
-Mmm hmm.
[Makes smacking noise]

06:45.208 --> 06:47.417
I only have twenty.
-That'll do.

06:47.458 --> 06:49.625
-See you there.

06:49.667 --> 06:52.125
[♪ Music]

06:52.166 --> 06:54.208
-Hey! You're not going
to believe this.

06:54.250 --> 06:57.917
A scout from Syracuse is coming
tomorrow to watch that kid
Terrence play.

06:57.959 --> 07:00.125
-Seriously? Are you
tight with this kid?

07:00.166 --> 07:02.166
-Yeah, real tight.
Like a brother.
-You mean like a father?

07:02.208 --> 07:04.417
-No, like a brother Bill.
That's how tight we are.

07:04.458 --> 07:06.667
-Would he say the same
thing about you?

07:06.709 --> 07:08.875
-Yes, he would say the
same thing. But listen...

07:08.917 --> 07:11.834
This means we're going to
get free tickets for March
Madness next year.

07:11.875 --> 07:15.041
-[Bill]: Tickets! Gerry, I don't
think you're seeing the big
picture here.

07:15.083 --> 07:17.125
You could be on the
bench next year.

07:17.166 --> 07:19.625
-What are you talking about?
-Good players bring their coach.

07:19.667 --> 07:22.125
Standard practice.
-Yeah I've heard of that,
I've heard of that.

07:22.166 --> 07:25.083
I've heard of that. You love the
coach, you bring them with you.

07:25.125 --> 07:27.667
Oh my god, I could be on the
bench in Syracuse next year.

07:27.709 --> 07:30.291
That would change my life.
-You could bring me too, right?

07:30.333 --> 07:33.041
-No Bill. What do you think we
do there at Syracuse?

07:33.083 --> 07:35.875
Just bring everybody on the
bench? That's not how it
works for us.

07:35.917 --> 07:37.959
Think!

07:38.709 --> 07:40.959
[♪ Music ]

07:41.000 --> 07:43.750
-[Gerry]: Ah, Ms. Giffer.
-Oh, call me Kathy Lee.

07:43.792 --> 07:46.792
-Your name's Kathy Lee Gifford?
-Kathy Lee Giffer.

07:46.834 --> 07:50.166
-Kathy Lee Gifford?
-Kathy Lee Giffer, no D.

07:50.208 --> 07:52.750
-I think there is a D, I think
it's Kathy Lee Gifford.

07:52.792 --> 07:55.000
-I think I know my name.

07:55.041 --> 07:58.166
-Of course you do, what am
I saying? Come on in here.

07:58.208 --> 08:00.208
Thank you for coming.

08:02.667 --> 08:04.917
What?

08:04.959 --> 08:08.333
Oh just a photo Terrence wanted
to grab of him and I before he
graduates.

08:08.375 --> 08:11.542
He says it's the T-man
with the G-man. I'm like...

08:11.583 --> 08:14.125
Anyway, why did I call you in?

08:14.166 --> 08:17.291
Um, I assume Terrence's
father is not in the picture?

08:17.333 --> 08:20.500
-No, he's at work.
-Biological father?

08:20.542 --> 08:22.709
-Yeah.

08:22.750 --> 08:25.834
-Well, Terrence has got a
big year. He's going off to
college by himself.

08:25.875 --> 08:28.083
I assume you're not going?
-Of course not.

08:28.125 --> 08:31.417
-You probably have three jobs.
-No, one job.

08:31.458 --> 08:34.333
-One job.
-One dad.

08:34.375 --> 08:36.333
-One dad.
-Yeah.

08:36.375 --> 08:38.792
-[Gerry clears his throat]:
College...

08:38.834 --> 08:41.083
Let me tell you about college.

08:41.125 --> 08:44.291
Sending a boy, vulnerable
like that...

08:45.500 --> 08:48.125
Drugs...
-Terrence doesn't do drugs.

08:48.166 --> 08:50.750
-Oh, you know everything
Terrence does?

08:50.792 --> 08:54.208
-Of course not.
-Kids go to college, they get
caught up in the wrong crowd.

08:54.250 --> 08:57.583
That leads to drugs.
Drugs leads to prostitution.

08:57.625 --> 09:02.667
And prostitutes leads to
Terrence becoming the
father of a crack child.

09:02.709 --> 09:05.834
And you are the grandmother
of that crack child.

09:05.875 --> 09:08.208
Do you want that to happen?
No you don't.

09:08.250 --> 09:10.417
So what happens is, I go.

09:10.458 --> 09:12.667
Package deal.

09:12.709 --> 09:15.875
Terrence, Mr. Duncan.
I'll coach.

09:15.917 --> 09:18.125
I don't care about that.

09:18.166 --> 09:21.834
I care about him. I want you
to give me your approval.

09:21.875 --> 09:24.291
And you will have somebody
there.

09:24.333 --> 09:28.375
An adult who cares just as much
about Terrence as you.

09:28.417 --> 09:32.667
Maybe more. I will be your
second set of eyes and ears.

09:32.709 --> 09:36.792
Like another parent, which
I'm kind of like now to him,
in a lot of ways.

09:36.834 --> 09:41.834
-Ummm, I've never really
considered anything like that,
Mr. Duncan.

09:41.875 --> 09:44.041
-Most parents don't.

09:44.083 --> 09:47.291
-So, I'm going to need to
talk that over with Terrence,
and my husband.

09:47.333 --> 09:49.625
-I'm going to tell Syracuse that
we're going to do this.

09:49.667 --> 09:51.875
-Yeah.
-Thank you Ms. Gifford.

09:51.917 --> 09:54.083
-Giffer.
-Yeah, I'm still not sure.

09:54.125 --> 09:56.500
We'll talk more about that.
-[Kathy Lee Quietly]: Okay.

09:56.542 --> 09:59.166
[♪ Music]

10:00.000 --> 10:02.208
[♪ Music]

10:04.375 --> 10:07.875
-Okay, seriously everybody?
Like, give me a break.

10:07.917 --> 10:10.750
-Feels good.
-Ugh, Simon, you too?

10:10.792 --> 10:14.333
-Oh, there he is.
Mr. Future Hug.

10:14.375 --> 10:17.834
Better light up that runway
Gerry, 'cause this hug's
coming in for a landing.

10:17.875 --> 10:20.458
-No, I am not into this.
You're not buying into this.

10:20.500 --> 10:22.875
-Can't deny, I was feeling down
in the dumps this morning.

10:22.917 --> 10:25.709
A couple hugs later, old
Simon is back.

10:25.750 --> 10:27.917
-Well I'll come back
when this is over.

10:27.959 --> 10:31.166
-No you don't, no you don't.
-Simon, Simon.

10:31.208 --> 10:34.333
-See, that's good right?
It's a nice feeling.
-Simon, can you please...

10:34.375 --> 10:36.625
-Can't deny it.
-Simon, Simon. Simon.

10:36.667 --> 10:39.000
-Let your worries wash away.
-Simon.

10:39.041 --> 10:43.583
-[Sings]: ♪ And let yourself
succumb to the hug.

10:43.625 --> 10:45.667
-Stop it.

10:48.542 --> 10:50.709
Weirdo.
[♪ Music]

10:50.750 --> 10:53.917
[♪ Music]

10:53.959 --> 10:56.333
[♪ Ambiant Music]

10:56.375 --> 10:59.125
[♪ Ambiant Music]

10:59.166 --> 11:01.458
[♪ Ambiant Music]

11:01.500 --> 11:04.166
-Oh, hey look, there's a
character in here named Lisa.

11:04.208 --> 11:08.625
And there's one called Simon.
-This is so exciting.

11:08.667 --> 11:12.333
-Bob and Lisa's love
was one for the ages.
[Laughs]

11:12.375 --> 11:15.959
This is gonna be great.
-Is Bob, Robert?

11:16.000 --> 11:18.959
Okay, why are all these
character's names our names?

11:19.000 --> 11:21.083
-Shh. It's about to start.
-But...

11:23.458 --> 11:25.667
[♪ Dramatic play music begins]

11:25.709 --> 11:28.000
[♪ Dramatic play music]

11:28.041 --> 11:30.250
-Oh, I should have
gone pee before this.

11:30.291 --> 11:32.834
[♪ Play music]

11:32.875 --> 11:35.291
[♪ Play music]

11:35.333 --> 11:37.709
[♪ Play music]

11:37.750 --> 11:41.000
[♪ Play music]

11:41.041 --> 11:43.375
-Lisa, what are you doing?

11:43.417 --> 11:47.625
It's a little distracting
while I'm trying to work.

11:47.667 --> 11:49.875
-I'll hold it.

11:49.917 --> 11:53.208
-[Crowd applause]
[Buzzer]

11:53.250 --> 11:55.750
-That was a good first half.
-Terrence is on fire.

11:55.792 --> 11:59.458
The whole team's amazing.
They almost coach themselves.

11:59.500 --> 12:02.542
-What do you mean? I coach them.
-Barely.

12:02.583 --> 12:05.500
-[Bobbi and man talk]
-There's the Syracuse scout.

12:08.750 --> 12:11.041
-Hey.
-[Gerry]: Hey.

12:11.083 --> 12:13.417
-Gerry, this is the scout from
Syracuse, Rodger Williamson.

12:13.458 --> 12:15.417
-[Gerry]: Hey, how are you?
-Hey, good.

12:15.458 --> 12:17.667
-You're a scout for basketball?
-Yeah.
-[Gerry]: Oh.

12:17.709 --> 12:20.625
-I'm not that tall, but you
don't need to be tall to watch
basketball.

12:20.667 --> 12:22.583
-[Bobbi laughs]
-[Gerry]: True.
-So...Right?

12:22.625 --> 12:24.792
-[Gerry]: Roger.
-Ah, Rodger, with a 'd'.

12:24.834 --> 12:27.542
-Where's the 'd' go?
-Right in the middle.
Rod. Ger.

12:27.583 --> 12:29.542
-Hyphenated. Rod-...
-[Rodger]: No, it's Rodger.

12:29.583 --> 12:31.750
-Rodger.
-Rod...Rodger, that's what
I said.

12:31.792 --> 12:34.000
-[Rodger]: Yeah it's cool.
-[Bobbi laughs]: Let's move on.

12:34.041 --> 12:36.208
-Anyway, Great first half.
-Aw.

12:36.250 --> 12:38.458
-So good, Terrence was on fire.
-He's special.

12:38.500 --> 12:40.625
And I gotta be honest,
there's a lot of schools
looking at us.

12:40.667 --> 12:43.375
-Us?
-We're a package deal.

12:43.417 --> 12:46.166
-What...what are you doing?
-We see this all the time.
It's fine.

12:46.208 --> 12:48.417
The package deal, right?
-[Gerry]: Yeah.

12:48.458 --> 12:50.709
Well his parents, there's
his mom. Hey mom.

12:50.750 --> 12:52.917
-[Mouths]: Me?
-[Gerry]: Haha, yeah.

12:52.959 --> 12:55.166
There she is. We had a talk...
-[Rodger]: Yeah.

12:55.208 --> 12:57.500
-About supervision and things
that kids can get into in
college.

12:57.542 --> 13:00.333
-Yeah, yeah. All the time.
People always pitch it to me.
For sure.

13:00.375 --> 13:02.834
-[Gerry]: Yeah.
-[Rodger]: Yeah, well I
will keep an eye on you then.

13:02.875 --> 13:05.625
-[Gerry]: Okay.
-'Cause if you're going to
be coaching with us next year...

13:05.667 --> 13:09.500
-Yeah. I'm going to go get
them ready for the second
half and show you what I do.

13:09.542 --> 13:11.959
[Gerry laughs]
-Sorry I'm late.

13:12.000 --> 13:14.250
-Oh, let's go. Thanks,
nice meeting you, Rod-Ger.
-Yeah.

13:14.291 --> 13:16.250
-Another time.
-Okay.

13:17.375 --> 13:21.083
-So, ah, what does he do?
-Yeah, you'll see.

13:21.125 --> 13:25.333
-Lisa, it's okay to have
erotically charged fantasies
about me.

13:25.375 --> 13:28.542
Just not here in school.
It's not appropriate.

13:28.583 --> 13:31.166
Same goes for you,
Ms. Trudy Dwyer.

13:31.208 --> 13:36.667
Just because you have huge pecs
and cutting quips doesn't mean
you can boss me around.

13:38.709 --> 13:41.667
Simon, drumroll please.

13:43.417 --> 13:46.709
-[Drumroll]

13:46.750 --> 13:50.083
-I'm sick and tired of people
not seeing the real me.

13:50.125 --> 13:54.583
That's why I've decided to...
drop all of my walls.

13:54.625 --> 13:55.875
-Howdy partner.

13:57.500 --> 14:02.375
-I feel so liberated. I'll
never hide behind my walls ever
again.

14:02.417 --> 14:07.959
-[Trudy laughs]: Wow. I owe
Bobbi an apolo-Jesus the
size of that thing.

14:08.000 --> 14:11.917
-[Claps]: Bravo! Bravo!

14:12.750 --> 14:15.000
Oh my gosh, what a twist.

14:15.041 --> 14:17.250
-You get the ending?
I don't get the ending.

14:17.291 --> 14:21.458
-I don't get any of it.
-Seriously everyone, thanks
so much for coming.

14:21.500 --> 14:25.625
Um, on behalf of all of us here
at the Schnitzelburg Community
Theatre Haus...

14:25.667 --> 14:28.458
-I love the theatre.
-It's been a real thrill
tonight.

14:28.500 --> 14:30.583
There is an after party which I
would like to extend the

14:30.625 --> 14:33.709
invitation to my colleagues
to join me for. Can you come,
guys?

14:33.750 --> 14:37.250
[Mouths]: Come guys.
But I'm afraid, not for the
rest of you in the house.

14:37.291 --> 14:39.500
Sincerely, thank you so much.
[Robert claps]: Thank you.

14:39.542 --> 14:41.542
[Robert claps]

14:41.583 --> 14:43.875
-[Gerry]: Time out ref,
time out. Bring it in.
[Whistle blows]

14:45.709 --> 14:48.291
-[Gerry takes a deep breath]

14:48.333 --> 14:50.667
Alright, ten point lead.

14:50.709 --> 14:53.625
Now you're going to see
something called coaching.

14:53.667 --> 14:55.709
We're gonna shut it down,
a little strategy.

14:55.750 --> 14:59.583
Okay? We're gonna control
the ball, we're gonna take
our time.

14:59.625 --> 15:03.083
-[Terrence]: Coach, isn't it a
bit early? We're only up by ten.

15:03.125 --> 15:05.500
-[Yells]: This is my team
Terrence. Not yours.

15:10.417 --> 15:14.083
How many of you have
seen 'Hoosiers'?
-Mmm, Barbara Hershey.

15:14.125 --> 15:17.417
-Nobody's seen 'Hoosiers'?
You call yourselves basketball
players? You gotta wat...

15:17.458 --> 15:21.625
Okay, forget it. Anyway, from
the 'Hoosiers' playbook with
my own little twist...

15:21.667 --> 15:23.959
We are gonna finish
off this game...

15:24.000 --> 15:28.166
By controlling the ball, making
12 passes before we take a shot.

15:28.208 --> 15:30.458
Is that clear?
-How many passes?

15:30.500 --> 15:34.333
-[Gerry]: 12 times. No shot.
I don't care if you're wide open
under the basket.

15:34.375 --> 15:38.333
You make a pass 'til we've
passed it 12 times.

15:38.375 --> 15:42.125
-This is rid...
-[Gerry loudly]: Terrence!
Do you want to play Terrence?

15:42.166 --> 15:44.834
This is my team Terrence,
you do not talk back.

15:46.834 --> 15:48.917
See that guy over there
in the suit? Is he looking?

15:54.166 --> 15:56.291
Alright. Let's bring it in.

15:57.375 --> 16:00.583
On three, Syracuse.
One, two, three Syracuse.

16:02.500 --> 16:06.250
Listen up, you're supposed
to say Syracuse there. Let's go.

16:06.291 --> 16:08.834
12 passes, 12 passes.
Say it to yourself.

16:08.875 --> 16:10.917
Let's do this.

16:13.417 --> 16:16.625
-Barbara was amazing
in 'Beaches'. Good rack.

16:18.583 --> 16:20.792
-[Whistle blows]
-Alright, that's it.

16:20.834 --> 16:24.166
Here we go, that's right.
Nice. Nice.

16:24.208 --> 16:27.542
Another one. Watch
the shot clock, good.

16:27.583 --> 16:29.959
[Gerry]: That's it.
Thank you.

16:30.000 --> 16:32.250
[Gerry]: That's it. That's it.
Another one.

16:32.291 --> 16:35.083
Good. Throwin' them.
We're throwin' them.

16:35.125 --> 16:37.917
Don't shoot that! Six more,
six more.

16:37.959 --> 16:40.250
-I think it's seven.
-That was six.

16:40.291 --> 16:42.500
That's only six. Don't shoot,
don't shoot.

16:42.542 --> 16:44.834
Bring it out, six more,
six more.
[Buzzer sounds]

16:44.875 --> 16:49.500
Okay. Okay. Little quicker,
little quicker. Alright?

16:49.542 --> 16:52.250
Where ya goin' Terrence?

16:52.291 --> 16:54.458
Hello?

16:54.500 --> 16:57.333
-Jack, in.
I'm out.

16:57.375 --> 17:00.000
-Okay, you're tired.
He's tired. Have a break.

17:00.041 --> 17:03.709
[♪ Music]
Okay, you'll go back
in when I say.

17:04.667 --> 17:07.625
[♪ Music]

17:07.667 --> 17:09.875
-Hey, Gerry.
-[Gerry]: Hey.

17:09.917 --> 17:12.709
-So, um, just a little update.
Terrence is gonna go to
Syracuse.

17:12.750 --> 17:14.917
-Okay. Good.

17:14.959 --> 17:17.709
I think Rodger feels the less
time you spend with Terrence
the better. Okay?

17:17.750 --> 17:19.959
-So, no, no.
-[Bobbi]: Mmm hmm?

17:20.000 --> 17:23.792
-Specifically...Specifically
what did Rod-Ger say?

17:23.834 --> 17:26.208
-He, specifically said...

17:27.000 --> 17:29.250
You are a cancer.

17:29.291 --> 17:33.208
-Did he say, you are a
prostate cancer? Or you
are a pancreatic cancer?

17:33.250 --> 17:35.500
Because prostate cancer
is treatable.

17:35.542 --> 17:37.709
-Right, you could be a
treatable cancer

17:37.750 --> 17:39.959
-Okay, then say that.
-You're a treatable cancer.

17:40.000 --> 17:41.917
-Okay. I guess I'm not
going with him, right?

17:41.959 --> 17:44.125
[Gerry quietly]: Okay.

17:44.166 --> 17:46.417
-It's not so bad.

17:46.458 --> 17:50.667
-Thank you...
Rod-Ger.

17:50.709 --> 17:52.750
-Hello fans.

17:52.792 --> 17:55.417
You guys missed a humdinger
of a party last night.
What happened?

17:55.458 --> 17:58.291
-It was, um...um...
-[Dwyer]: I had an online
course I'm studying for.

17:58.333 --> 18:00.583
-Yeah, I didn't want to go,
so...

18:00.625 --> 18:03.583
-Doesn't matter.
What'd ya think?

18:03.625 --> 18:05.959
-Why was I the transvestite?
-[Trudy]: Wait a minute.

18:06.000 --> 18:09.166
Why were WE the transvestite?
-What?

18:09.208 --> 18:11.583
-Trudy Dwyer.
-Oh.

18:11.625 --> 18:14.834
-And do you have those
weird fantasies about me?

18:14.875 --> 18:18.542
-No! Those were just the names
that popped into my head
when I was...

18:18.583 --> 18:22.166
Writing it up on my
typewriter. Is that what's
goin' on here? Names?

18:22.208 --> 18:26.625
-Well, that and you might have
given us a heads up that you
were going to be naked.

18:26.667 --> 18:28.917
-[Lisa laughs]: Yeah.
-I wasn't naked.

18:28.959 --> 18:32.458
The character of Bob was.
Take it up with him.
Maybe he's still in here.

18:32.500 --> 18:34.917
Hello Bob? It's Robert.
-Oh.

18:34.959 --> 18:37.208
-You guys don't get art.
That's the problem here.

18:37.250 --> 18:40.458
You're the reason that theatre
in this country is DYING-A!

18:40.500 --> 18:42.709
-Oh yeah. We are.

18:42.750 --> 18:44.792
-Ohhhh, there he is.

18:44.834 --> 18:47.834
I laughed, I cried.
Brilliant performance.

18:47.875 --> 18:51.500
Got another ticket for tonight.
-Whoo, thank you Simon.

18:51.542 --> 18:54.125
See, someone who understands,
culture.
-[Lisa laughs]

18:54.166 --> 18:56.959
-[Dwyer laughs]: I still don't
understand why I was the
transvestite.

18:57.000 --> 19:00.208
-I get it.
-Explain it...To him.

19:00.250 --> 19:04.291
-Oh yeah, it's like you guys
coming together to form a
tasty combo.

19:04.333 --> 19:06.500
-Half chocolate and half...
-You don't...

19:06.542 --> 19:08.750
-White person.
-[Robert]: Have to get it.
It's art.

19:08.792 --> 19:12.333
-It's art.
-I still don't understand why we
had to see your piece.

19:12.375 --> 19:15.166
-Can't wait to see your
piece again.
-[Robert]: Aw.

19:15.208 --> 19:18.166
[♪ Music,
Glenn Morrison, Goodbye]

19:18.208 --> 19:21.291
-There you are. Hey Terrence.
-Hey Coach.

19:21.333 --> 19:24.875
-[Gerry sighs]
[♪ Music]: ♪ It's enough,
that I know ♪

19:24.917 --> 19:27.834
-So...
-So...

19:27.875 --> 19:29.834
-Guess we're not going to
Syracuse together.

19:29.875 --> 19:33.041
-No, we're not.
-But you are.

19:33.083 --> 19:36.583
You're going. You're going to
be a Syracuse Orangeman.

19:36.625 --> 19:38.625
[Gerry]: And that's what counts.

19:39.834 --> 19:42.041
Listen, I don't know if it's
possible but...

19:42.083 --> 19:45.625
But maybe I could get some
March Madness tickets when
you're there.

19:45.667 --> 19:49.125
-Probably not. My parents
don't want me talking to you.
-Yeah, I get it.

19:49.166 --> 19:51.959
But hey, nobody cuts oranges
like you Coach.

19:52.000 --> 19:55.291
♪ Now I wanna know,
what it took to leave me ♪

19:55.333 --> 19:59.917
♪ Now I, I wanna know ♪

